    {
      "text": "Sansara Naga (サンサーラ・ナーガ, Sansara Naga) is a series of Japan-exclusive video games. The first title was released in 1990 for the Family Computer, four years later Sansara Naga 2 was released for the Super Famicom, and finally in 2001 Sansara Naga 1x2 was released for the Game Boy Advance.\nThe characters were designed by Tamakichi Sakura.\nDespite the game being Japanese, the title is Sanskrit, meaning \"Cycle of the Serpent\" (Sanskrit: संसारनाग, romanized: \"Samsara Naga\").",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
